value.0: This red-skinned Lizardman bolsters an outlandish muscular body compared to its athletic-toned bretherin. Siz'lanir is one of the few Lizardman to leave the community in terms of adventure, however recent times has drawn him back home. He now works his hardest to provide for his kin in any way possible after becoming their leader.
Sizzle Armour
Bastard Sword of Pain
Tattered Cloak
Siz'lanir
A griffon is an intelligent beast with the body of a lion and the wings, forelegs, and head of an eagle. These majestic creatures are often used as heraldry symbols and mounts by skilled knights.

This red-skinned female Lizardfolk has a haughty air about her, but she wears the mark of Siz'lanir's tribe with pride.

Made from the severed tendrils of carrion crawlers, these whips are most commonly used by slavers and the like. Yet since sold in open markets, sometimes an adventurer will find one in her hands as well.  Like many whips available in the Underdark, these come in a variety of strengths and potencies.  Use with caution.
Greater Tendril Whip

Made from reinforced wyvern leather, this powerful belt is inlaid with four emeralds which act as focii for the magic which binds it. It protects the wearer from all manner of traps and snares, as well as providing a boost to the wearer's vitality.

It smells vaguely of the Quagmire swamps.

Truly something that fell from the heavens above!

This hunk of unpolished rock fits into very few travel packs and most definately requires a couple hands to cart around. Hot gas spews out from it's veins, which could burn the many hands needed to transport such a find.

It'd be best to inquire with an expert wizard as to how it's powers may be used.
Mythal Reagent, Divine

A unique crossbow of Gnomish origin, though it was acquired after we thwarted the plans of an evil collector, so its exact origin is unknown. What IS known is that this weapon is a one-of-a-kind prototype. It contains two core components, the Crossbow itself and its self-generating ammo dispenser that can dispense unique ammunition bound to this crossbow once a day.

Use the unset item on another item in your inventory. This item will be stored for future spawning. 

Use the item on yourself when you stored all the items you want tot spawn. This fixes the item so it can be used for spawning. You can store up to 6 items, and the item will be automatically fixed when you reach this number.

Mind that the widget accepts any item as it is, including imported DM items.

Suggestion: Rename the widged when it is fixed.
